# Orchestration (Project North Star)

## What this repo is
Ryan Winzenburg’s portfolio site (React + Vite + TypeScript) with long-form articles. Optimize for:
- high-quality, readable UI in dark theme
- strict TypeScript correctness
- consistent article layouts (spacing, lists, blockquotes, images)
- fast iteration without regressions

## Environment + commands
- **Package manager**: pnpm
- **Dev**: `pnpm dev`
- **Typecheck**: `pnpm check`
- **Build**: `pnpm build`

## How to work in this repo
- Prefer **small, surgical changes** with lints/typecheck kept green.
- When changing UI, **match existing patterns** (Tailwind v4 utilities, dark theme).
- When changing article pages, update both:
  - the article page file in `client/src/pages/articles/`
  - the article card metadata in `client/src/pages/Articles.tsx` when hero/excerpt/reading time changes

## Quality gates (hard)
- **No `any`** (explicit or implicit). If data is `unknown`, define a type + type guard.
- **No leftover `console.log`** in production code.
- **All `<img>` must have descriptive `alt`** (empty alt only when truly decorative).
- **API calls**: include error handling; don’t silently swallow failures.

## Style + content guardrails
- Tailwind is **v4**. Don’t apply v2/v3 config patterns.
- Avoid “template-y” writing across articles (don’t reuse the same hook/transition phrases repeatedly).

